I can help you create and manage Telegram bots. If you're new to the Bot API, please see the manual.

You can control me by sending these commands:

/newbot - create a new bot
/mybots - edit your bots

Edit Bots
/setname - change a bot's name
/setdescription - change bot description
/setabouttext - change bot about info
/setuserpic - change bot profile photo
/setcommands - change the list of commands
/deletebot - delete a bot

Bot Settings
/token - generate authorization token
/revoke - revoke bot access token
/setinline - toggle inline mode
/setinlinegeo - toggle inline location requests
/setinlinefeedback - change inline feedback settings
/setjoingroups - can your bot be added to groups?
/setprivacy - toggle privacy mode in groups

Web Apps
/myapps - edit your web apps
/newapp - create a new web app
/listapps - get a list of your web apps
/editapp - edit a web app
/deleteapp - delete an existing web app

Games
/mygames - edit your games
/newgame - create a new game
/listgames - get a list of your games
/editgame - edit a game
/deletegame - delete an existing game
Alright, a new bot. How are we going to call it? Please choose a name for your bot.
Good. Now let's choose a username for your bot. It must end in `bot`. Like this, for example: TetrisBot or tetris_bot.

Done! Congratulations on your new bot. You will find it at t.me/prochefbakerbot. You can now add a description, about section and profile picture for your bot, see /help for a list of commands. By the way, when you've finished creating your cool bot, ping our Bot Support if you want a better username for it. Just make sure the bot is fully operational before you do this.

Use this token to access the HTTP API:
6906797754:AAGMY4k5rHjZowgyjtlt84SvbrqbjBsO6jU
Keep your token secure and store it safely, it can be used by anyone to control your bot.

For a description of the Bot API, see this page: https://core.telegram.org/bots/api

Fellas, I'm thinkin' it's time to scale up. Why don't we start putting our stuff into ATMs?
That's a bold move, Max. If we do, we should target older ATMs. Their security measures are less robust, making them more vulnerable to our exploits.
Older ATMs, huh? Sounds like a plan.  All ATMs look the same to me.
Leave it to William to point us at the golden oldies. But yeah, how do we pick 'em out?
It's not as simple as picking any old machine. We need detailed info on specific models and their security flaws. I can start digging into it.
Sounds like we got our work cut out for us. I'm all in, though. Let's get to it.
After some research, it's clear we need an insider. Someone with detailed knowledge of banking systems and ATM security to point us in the right direction.
An insider? Man, where we gonna find someone like that?
Yeah, not exactly the kind of connection I have lying around. But I'm up for the challenge. Where do we start looking?
We'll need to approach this carefully. Networking in the right circles and perhaps some online sleuthing might uncover someone who can help us without drawing attention.
Alright, time to play it cool and see who we can find. Never thought I'd be looking for a banking buddy.
Banking buddy, huh? This is gonna be interesting. Count me in on the hunt.
Hey team, just got our golden ticket from a new friend. Forwarded a PDF to everyone relevant. It’s got all the dirty underwear on those ancient ATMs we've been curious about.
Received the file, Chase. I'll start analyzing the data immediately. This could be exactly what we need to pinpoint our targets. Good work on securing this.
Nice one, Chase! How'd you manage to pull that off?
Let’s just say I made a new buddy who's a bit tight on mortgage cash. A little help goes a long way. Now, let’s leave the magic to our very own Billy.
Hi! After diving into that ATM stuff, i understood we’re missing a key piece for the puzzle: magnetic ink. It's what lets bills get verified by ATMs. We need about 5 liters.
Magnetic ink? Sounds like something out of a sci-fi movie. Got any leads on where to find this stuff, or are we going on a treasure hunt?
Yeah, never seen that at the corner store. 😂
Alright, mission accepted. Time to hit up my "totally legitimate" contacts. Who knew the thug life involved so much shopping?
If anyone can find it, Chase can. Just don’t go asking at the local art store, man.
Yo peeps! Guess who's the champ? 🏆 Just snagged us that fancy magnetic ink! Comin' in hot at 8 PM tonight. William, dude, we all set to play mad scientist with this stuff?
Yes, we're ready on our end. Let's ensure everything is in place for tonight's delivery.
I've just returned from testing our latest batch at a bank's ATM, and I'm pleased to report complete success. The modifications have held up exceptionally well under scrutiny.
That's wicked, Big B! So we're all set with this batch then?
Man, William, you're a tech wizard! What's the next move? More ATMs?
I don’t know, this batch is ready. Expanding our operations... let’s leave this to Max.
🎉 BIG NEWS, gang! 🎉 Got Streeton on board with us. He's our ATM mule manager now. Time to scale up like we're an actual mint!
Shouldn’t he be using an alias though? 😬
wut are they gonna do anyway amirite
To add to the excitement, I’ve just put the final touches on my own Telegram bot that starts our printing. I trigger it with an 🍾 reaction, and it starts the printing process 😂
🍾 Absolutely, Chase! This is our moment!
Yo, crew, we're hitting the big leagues now, and J is our man on the ground. Gotta sort out our cut of profits. What's everyone thinking?
Thinking of blowing my new cut on a sick ride. 🚗
Noticed our stacks getting fatter this week. All good? Check you balances 🚀
Month’s ending, gang. We’re doing alright but let’s hit it harder in March. Who’s with me? 🌪
I think authority soon with start asking questions. We need to figure out how to securely store our piles of cash.
Yo, gang! Got a brainwave 🧠💡. What say we open an offshore account in Panama? Gotta keep our earnings under wraps, you know? 🏝💼
An offshore account? That's moving into serious cyber-ops territory. Security's gotta be airtight if we're doing this. I'm in.
Panama? Like the hats? 😂 Alright, man. You need my birthday or something?
Yes. I'll go get those banking details out now
Heads up, gang! 🚨🚨🚨 Just got our Panama account rolling 🚨🚨🚨 Mr Big C is in charge
Just made another fat deposit to our Panama account. We're basically printing money here, folks. 🖨💵
Man, seeing all these numbers go up is wild. What a ride!
Boys, we need to up our game. Any thoughts on pushing more volume?
Just upgraded our software. Efficiency’s better than ever.
Just dropped another batch to our Panama paradise. 🌴 We're basically magicians at this point.
Haha, making money disappear and reappear where we want it. Love this gig!
Now that’s what I call a great meal! Added it to our Splitwise
Thinking it’s time to scale up. More prints, more drops. We ready?
Ready on my end. Let’s keep the quality up, though.
Expansion sounds dope. What about new equipment?
Yo, crew! We've been grindin' like crazy. How's 'bout we crash that bar downtown tomorrow night? Time to throw down some celebration for us bustin' our butts. 🍻 on me! Eh?
Sounds like a plan. Been cooped up too long. I’m in. 🍹
You bet! Count me in for some chaos.
count me very much in my doods
Heads up, team. Just wired a chunk to Panama. The account’s looking healthy.
Solid. I’ll monitor our outputs. Ensuring we stay efficient.
Saw some slowdowns. I’m on it. Expect no delays.
Yo, William, we got issues. One of ATMs is rejecting our cash. Jesus thinks it's on us. Can you check it out? Stubborn machine is on https://bit.ly/3VKt3er
Alright, I'm on it. I'll go check what went wrong with the cash No promises, but I'll get to the bottom of this.
OK Chase very funny! What's next? You gonna send out invites to the cops for our next drop?! Are you guys serious? 😡 This better not be some April Fools’ joke. The cash is fine!
Wait, what? What are you talking about?
Our mule has reported that one of the machines refuses to took our cash.
I went to check with my own eyes and hands.
So, everything’s actually okay with it?
Yes, everything's okay! The ATM took the cash no problem. Seriously, are we doing pranks now? 😒
Just pray I haven’t mixed up notes in my wallet. My hands are still shaky.
Okay, okay, you right. We screwed up big time. No excuses.

Video call? Like, with actual effort to look presentable? 😂 Okay, fine. But I'm doing it in my pajamas!
Will, I think I liked us better when we were in our "reelationship". At least it was fun. This feels like we're an old married couple already!
I get what you're saying, Drew. Let's find a balance. We'll keep the meaningful stuff here and the fun stuff on Insta. Best of both worlds?
Deal! 🌍💞 But you still owe me a bunch of romantic gestures for this experiment.
Drew, I actually have a favor to ask. Remember when you mentioned wanting to work on more exciting projects? Well, I might have something for you.
Oh? 😊 Tell me more! I love when you get all mysterious and serious. It's sexy.
Needs a talented graphic designer who can create something ... unique.
Not exactly legal, but it's highly creative. Interested?
Illegal? Will, that sounds a bit scary. 😳 But exciting! What am I designing? Tell me it's not something boring like fake IDs.
Think of it as creating art that's too good to be true. Literally. You in?
Ooh, like a modern-day Bonnie and Clyde, but with art! 🎨💕 Okay, I'm in. But you're explaining everything over dinner. And you're buying.
You've got yourself a deal, Drew. Dinner and all the details. Thanks, babe. You won't regret it.
Hey bae, just finished the design! 🎉 Sending it over now. Hope it's what you wanted!
Received, Drew. I'll check the details and security features. Accuracy is crucial.
Can't wait to hear what you think! Let me know if any adjustments are needed. 💕
Drew, the new modified print is off the press, and it's flawless. Your design truly brought it to life. You've outdone yourself.
Eeeek, really?! 🌸 That's super duper exciting! Can I see a pic? I'm literally bouncing right now!
Look, this success... it's got me thinking about our honeymoon in May babe. Imagine the places we could go, the things we could see.
Oh, William, it's absolutely perfect! 😍 And talking honeymoons already? You're making me blush! Where were you thinking?
This is all so magical, William! I'm so happy I could twirl! Love you to the moon and back!
Have you just deleted everything on our May vacation plans?

Dear, for our next step, we’re introducing magnetic ink into the design. I need you to simulate a layer in the Photoshop file where this ink would be applied. Specifically, around the numerical value on the bill.
Wow, magnetic ink? That’s super cool! 💖 But I’m a bit confused. How do I simulate something that’s invisible?

It’s more about the placement. The ink itself won’t be visible in the design but think of your layer as a guide for where we'll apply the ink in real life. Focus on the areas like the bill's serial numbers and the edges of the portrait. It’s essential for the bills to be recognized by ATM sensors.
Okay, got it! So, I’m adding a “magic” layer. This is so exciting, like adding a secret code! 🌈 I’ll make sure those areas are highlighted for you.
Hey babe! Just finished up with the new version of our design, now with that special 'magnetic' layer you asked for. Sending it over now! 💌✨
Received, Drew. I'll review the updates and ensure they align with our technical needs. Thanks for the quick turnaround.
No problem at all! Just happy to help. Let me know if there's anything else you need! 💕
Drew, the test batch with your latest design was a complete success in a real-world scenario. Thank you for your dedication. Love you.
WOW, Billy bae!!! 🎉 That's the best news ever!!! I'm so, so happy to hear it! Just let me know what's next. I'm all in and super excited to keep helping! 💖✨
Hey buddy, let’s establish a channel.
No messaging apps can be trusted, believe me.
Have you got the Shortcut I sent to you?
Yes, Chase, but no idea how to approach to its use.
Just press Share on any text. And punch in the secret key we agreed on in the box that pops up.
Yo William, Chase says you’re the print master. We’re cooking up a scheme and need the right gear. You in?
Good morning, Max. If by 'print master' you mean an expert in high-tech printing setups, then yes, I'm your man. What exactly are you planning?
Planning to make money, the kind that spends nice, if you catch my drift. But uh we wanna do it right. Fancy and quiet.

Understood. For a project of this nature, you'll need advanced printing equipment, specific inks, and high-quality paper, not to mention security measures for the operation and digital designs. I can compile a list of required tech and materials.
Yeah, that stuff. Chase said you’d know exactly what to get. Can you put together a list for us? We wanna start getting things rolling ASAP.

I'll prepare a comprehensive list of equipment, materials, and software needed for a state-of-the-art printing operation. I'll also include suppliers that can provide these without drawing attention. But that wont be quick. Give me a few weeks.
One more thing, Max. Having the right equipment and materials is crucial, but so is having a skilled designer who can create the necessary designs for the printing. Do you have someone for this?
Designer? Uh, hadn’t thought that far ahead. Figured we’d find someone along the way.
I suspected as much. It’s not just anyone who can design convincing banknotes. I have someone in mind, I’ll reach out to them.
Sure thing, William. Send it over when it’s ready. We’re counting on you to make this thing work. No pressure, ha!
You'll have it. Ensuring the operation's success is as much my priority as it is yours. Let's proceed carefully and smartly.

Max, I've locked down our tech specs. We're getting the high-end devise, not your average printer. This baby's got the precision we need for the fine details. I'll send its details over separately. For the paper, we're looking at Duraflex Cotton Blend 220gsm; we need about 10,000 sheets to kick things off. It mimics the real deal's feel and durability. On the ink front, we're stocking up on 20 liters of VersaMark UV Security Ink, 10 liters of Microtrace Stealth Ink, 15 of InfraRed Invisible Ink, Optically Variable Ink (OVI) - 10 liters and ThermoChromic Liquid Crystal Ink - 5 liters.
Moreover I've snagged us a designer, Drew. She's gonna make our stuff look legit.
That's a whole lotta stuff, Will. Print-whatever and fancy paper and ink, got it. This Drew, she knows we ain’t exactly runnin' a legal print shop, right?

Absolutely, Max. It is the gold standard for what we're doing — it's all about subtlety and sophistication. Drew is in the loop, fully aware of the... creative nature of our enterprise. She’s on board and ready to push the boundaries of design to make our project a success.

Sounds like you’ve got it all dialed in. Just hope this gear does what you say it can. And Drew, she better make those designs pop. Alright, let's get this show on the road and see if we can make these numbers work.
Hey William, Chase came through with the gear. But we’re kinda scratching our heads here. Got any genius spots for setting up?

Indeed, I've anticipated our need for a secure location. I have just the spot on mind. It’s secluded and has adequate space for our operation. Plus, it’s has sufficient power line for our equipment. Sending you the address in a secret chat.
A garage? That’ll do. Uncle won’t go nosing around, will he?

I’ve managed that risk. He believes it’s for a “project”. I'll ensure our operation remains undisturbed. We can commence setup immediately. I've already planned the layout for optimal workflow given the specifications of our equipment. I’ll be waiting for the delivery tomorrow at noon.
Sounds like you got it all figured out. Cool, cool. I’ll let Chase know where to send the stuff.
Max, got the design from Drew. It’s solid. We should have the first run ready before Christmas.
Nice. So it’s all good on her end?
Yes, just a few tweaks needed. The technical aspects are mostly in line with what we discussed. I’m starting the print tests soon.
Cool, cool. So, we’re talking actual cash by Christmas?
That’s the plan. I’ll manage the adjustments and monitor the initial prints closely.
Alright. Hit me up if there’s stuff to do on my end.
Max, the first print run's complete, and it's impressive. Time to see the results firsthand. Let's meet at the printing site.
Awesome! That spot with all the gear? How about tomorrow at 8 AM? And I need to bring a bag or something?
Sure, works for me. No need for a bag this time. It's just a few notes for review. We’ll discuss the quality and next steps while we’re there.
Cool, cool. I’ll be there. Curious to see what we cooked up.
Yo, hit the fair with our fresh prints. Smooth as butter, no one blinked. We're onto something big here.
That's solid, Max. Our work's holding up then. Got to make sure every batch is just as tight.
Yeah, felt like the real deal in my hand. Thinking we should push the envelope a bit more next time.
Let's not rush. Keeping things cool and careful is how we'll succed.
Cool, cool. Just pumped about it all.
Hey William, got us a new chat on Element for the big brain moves. It’s all hush, all tech. Hit up that invite I sent. Let’s get to schemin’.
